All Africa Games to Act as Olympic Qualifiers
JOHANNESBURG , November 15 ( Xinhua ) -- The 7th All Africa Games to be staged in South Africa next year will be used by 10 sporting codes as Olympic qualification events , a senior African sports official said Sunday .
Association of National Olympic Committees of Africa ( ANOCA ) president Jean Claude Ganga told a press conference here this arrangement would prevent duplication and save money for the continent 's sports bodies .
The All Africa Games , slated from September 10 to 19 , 1999 , will attract some 5,000 to 6,000 athletes all around the continent .
Dan Moyo , chairman of the All Africa Games ' sports commission , which is facilitating the program for the event , said an in loco inspection Saturday of venues earmarked for next year 's meeting had left SCSA officials " very satisfied . "
Many of the events , he added , would be staged in Soweto black township , where existing facilities would be upgraded to Games standard .
The operational costs of staging the event were estimated at around 107 million rand ( 18.6 million U.S. dollars ) .
Of this , the South African government had committed 40 million rand ( 6.9 million U.S. dollars ) , while the private sector had already come up with 30 million rand ( 5.2 million U.S. dollars ) .
